# Artifactory + Xray

Auth: Bearer scoped Access Token.
- `ARTIFACTORY_BASE_URL` = full Artifactory base, e.g. `https://siemens.jfrog.io/artifactory`
- `ARTIFACTORY_TOKEN` = scoped Access Token (needs `system:info/storage:r` + repo read)

Xray endpoints are routed automatically: paths starting with `/xray/`
go to `<host-root>/xray/...` (host root = base minus trailing `/artifactory`).

## Artifactory endpoints
- `GET /api/storageinfo` — totals, file-store, per-repo summary
- `GET /api/repositories?type=local|remote|virtual|federated`
- `GET /api/storage/{repoKey}` — per-repo detail
- `GET /api/system/ping`, `/api/system/version`
- `POST /api/search/aql` (text/plain body) — top largest, stale artifacts, etc.

## Xray endpoints
- `GET /xray/api/v1/system/ping`
- `POST /xray/api/v1/violations`
- `POST /xray/api/v1/summary/artifact` — vuln summary by path

## Proxy
`supabase/functions/artifactory/index.ts` — handles auth + Xray routing,
supports text/plain for AQL.
Client: `src/lib/artifactory.ts`. Hooks: `src/hooks/useArtifactory.ts`.
